Text: How am I, I am well thank you. How old am I, I am in my early 20s. My name is Daisy Leondrea.

Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today, is because I have broken my glasses when I was at the gym so I need to buy new glasses but I wanted to get an eye test done before I buy one to make sure I get the right prescription. As you can see, I have fixed them with some tape but its not exactly good cosmetically. I can√ït see without my glasses and now that they are broken, I have mostly been wearing my Dailies contact lenses which I have been wearing over 5 years. The contact lens prescription is RE: -7.00 and LE: -6.50. My last appointment to get my contact lens prescription was only 2 weeks ago. My last full eye examination for glasses was about a year and half ago. My vision with my contact lenses is clearer than with my glasses. My distance vision and near vision are still okay with my glasses but perhaps not quite as good as it used to me. As you can see I am wearing my glasses right now.
Without my glasses or contact lenses my vision is awful, I can't see anything really.

I am not experiencing any eye problems such as eye strain, redness, double vision or blurriness. I don√ït have any flashing lights but I get occasional floaters in my vision which have been around for 5 years in both eyes. I usually see the floaters in the afternoons. I haven√ït noticed any changes in the floaters and they haven√ït been bothering me.

I am very happy with my contact lenses, I wear them all day pretty much but I do take them out at night. I wear them about 14 hours a day on average I guess. My eyes get a bit dry when I wear my contact lenses for too long. When I'm not wearing my contact lenses I have to wear my glasses, I'm blind without them.

General health, my health is completely fine; I don√ït have any health problems I√ïm not taking any medications or have any allergies. I don't have diabetes or raised blood pressure as far as I know. I haven't had my eyes patched as a child, I don't have a lazy eye either.

My hobbies include trying to keep myself healthy by going to the gym and walking. They gym is in Cardiff and I get a special discounted price because I know the manager there. I go to the gym about 3 times a week, you have to keep fit you know! My favourite walks are in the Brecon Beacons, the area around the waterfalls is the best. I am not a car driver, I never got my driving test.

Ocular history, 3 years ago I had laser treatment at the hospital done for lattice degeneration to prevent retinal detachment in BE and I haven√ït had any problems since. In the past, I had laser treatment in my eyes for lattice degeneration. It was a bit unpleasant having the laser treatment but I'm glad I had it done the idea of having a retinal detachment worries me. I did have a bad eye infection, which was caused by my contact lenses I think about 4 years ago. I had to take some eye drops for the eye infection but it cleared up okay after a week or so.
As far as I know, I don√ït have any ocular problems such as AMD, cataracts or glaucoma.

Everyone in my family is healthy, they don't have anything like high blood pressure or diabetes as far as I know. Concerning my families eye health, I think they are all fine, there are no ocular problems.
For a living I work as a dental student, that's my occupation right now. I spend around 5-6 hours on my laptop and about 3 hours on my phone because I just love social media, a lot of screen time!
I don√ït like the smell of smoke so I don√ït smoke. I don't drink alcohol but I do like a good cup of tea.
I do not have anything else to add. I don't have anything more to add.
